.TH GOTOMUX 1 "2025" "gotomux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gotomux \- fuzzy tmux session picker
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gotomux
[\fB\-f\fR [\fIname\fR]]
[\fB\-e\fR [\fIname\fR]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gotomux
is a fuzzy tmux session picker.
It presents live sessions, saved presets, and zoxide paths in a
filterable TUI.
Press Enter to connect, or use keybindings to kill, freeze, edit, and delete.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-f [\fIname\fR]
Freeze a session into a preset.
If
.I name
is omitted, freezes the current tmux session, or prompts to pick one.
.TP
.B \-e [\fIname\fR]
Edit a preset in $EDITOR.
If
.I name
is omitted, opens an interactive picker.
.TP
.B \-h
Show help text.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.TP
.B type
Filter (fzf-style matching, Vietnamese diacritics folded).
.TP
.B Enter
Connect.
.TP
.B Ctrl-n / Ctrl-p
Next / previous.
.TP
.B Ctrl-u / Ctrl-w
Clear query / delete word.
.TP
.B Ctrl-x
Kill active session.
.TP
.B Ctrl-f
Freeze selection into preset + shape.
.TP
.B Ctrl-t
Set sticky shape.
.TP
.B Ctrl-e / Ctrl-d
Edit / delete preset.
.TP
.B Esc / Ctrl-c
Cancel.
.TP
.B ?
Toggle help.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B TMUX
When set, the picker uses an alt-screen popup and hides the current session
from the active list.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_DATA_HOME/gotomux/state.db
SQLite store (presets, shapes, usage, placement).
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/gotomux/shapes/<label>\-\-<id>.json
Shape backups.
.SH SEE ALSO
tmux(1), zoxide(1)
